The Chairman of Benue State Independent Electoral Commission, Tersoo Loko, on Sunday declared the Peoples Democratic Party the winner of the local government election held in the state. The local government election was held across the 23 local government areas without the participation of the All Progressives Congress. The APC had in February announced that it would not participate in the election as it asked its members to boycott the exercise. Announcing the results of the election on Sunday at the BSIEC office located along Ankpa Road, Makurdi, Loko declared the PDP as the winner of the 23 chairmanship seats and all councillorship seats in 276 council wards across the state, leaving none for other parties. He said five political parties namely; the African Action Congress, the PDP, All Progressives Grand Alliance, Labour party and Social Democratic Party took part in the exercise. The BSIEC chairman said the election was devoid of violence, and was free and fair in all the local government areas. Earlier, the state command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps said it deployed 1250 personnel across the state to maintain peace, order and to provide strong security coverage before, during and after the local government election. The state commandant, Phillip Okoh, stated that the command was aware of the security challenges in the state but promised that the corps would leave nothing to chance to ensure the security of lives and property and guarantee peace across the state. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com